Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.76,0:01:34.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.30,0:01:40.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At long last, the time has come for my friend\nto bid farewell to things of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.17,0:01:44.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sincerity. Trust.\NFriendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.81,0:01:52.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All those virtues, all those wonderful things\nthat we possess during childhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.58,0:01:55.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he has now cast into the darkness\nof space, bidding them adieu.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.05,0:02:04.01,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 16:\NScandal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.03,0:02:14.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Planet Janina invaded\nby Empire 15 years ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.90,0:02:17.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Space Forces\nhurriedly deployed,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.14,0:02:19.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"...commissioned officer makes\nsecret deal with Empire."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.64,0:02:22.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Paris has been shaken to its\nfoundation by this scandal...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.44,0:02:24.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...involving lead presidential\ncandidate General Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.52,0:02:28.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take me to Space Forces\nImperial Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.41,0:03:00.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Albert de Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.05,0:03:02.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's the son\nof the general!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.69,0:03:12.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Were you and your family aware of what\nyour father had done on Janina?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.69,0:03:16.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Was the General trying to get at\nthe Pasha of Janina's fortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:17.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ow! Hey, watch it!\NDon't push!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.10,0:03:20.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of your\nfather's shameful acts?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:22.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.14,0:03:23.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The General should apologize\nto the people of Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:24.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:24.66,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Issue an apology!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.77,0:03:26.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've heard rumors to the effect that\nyour parents are from Marseilles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.64,0:03:29.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about that!\NDidn't I tell you to stand aside?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.41,0:03:32.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are rumors going around that\nyour family isn't really of nobility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.41,0:03:34.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is it safe to assume that they\nfalsified their background?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.72,0:03:38.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be rude! I've had about enough\nof you people insulting my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.59,0:03:42.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Insulting?! The ones who have been insulted\nall these years are us! The citizens of Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.92,0:03:47.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're the son of a traitor who colluded with the\nenemy and sold out the Pasha out of greed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:54.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Viscount Morcerf?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.04,0:03:56.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's my father?!\NTell me where my father is!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:04:01.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You came in through the front gate?\NWhat a foolish thing to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:04.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me to the back entrance.\NIt's not safe for you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.58,0:04:07.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father! Where is he?\NLet me speak with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.08,0:04:12.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, he is preoccupied with\ndealing with everything that has come up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.59,0:04:14.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so I believe that he might\nnot return here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.59,0:04:15.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.99,0:04:20.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, give my father this message.\NThere is something I want to discuss with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.56,0:04:24.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And also tell my father\nthat I believe in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:26.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.95,0:04:41.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.39,0:04:48.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have done everything\nthat I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:52.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, explaining things to the\NNational Assembly may prove difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.59,0:04:55.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Their discussions are already centering\naround issuing subpoenas for witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.13,0:04:57.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.\NYou can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:00.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your son was\njust here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.17,0:05:04.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As per your orders, I told him\nthat you were not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:06.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.51,0:05:11.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your son said that he\nbelieves in his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.13,0:05:27.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!\NQuick, get in!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.20,0:05:36.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.07,0:05:39.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think you're going\nat a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.31,0:05:41.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you do as\nyou're told for once?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.04,0:05:43.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.68,0:05:44.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.18,0:05:47.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Was I talking to myself when I ordered\nyou people again and again...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.75,0:05:49.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...not to let my daughter\nout of the house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.65,0:05:50.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Call security!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.65,0:05:52.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Monsieur!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.65,0:05:52.05,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.22,0:05:54.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something terrible has happened to my\nfriend's family, and you're telling me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.19,0:05:56.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...to look the\nother way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.86,0:06:00.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You little fool! If you went out there now,\nthose journalists would eat you alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.53,0:06:04.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They'll write about your relationship with Albert,\nblending fact and fiction until it becomes a farce,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:06.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and we'll be made into toys\nfor the public's amusement!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.87,0:06:08.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.34,0:06:10.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about\nany of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:15.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, this matter isn't\njust about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.38,0:06:20.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't tolerate anything that might lower\nyour value, whatever it might be!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.08,0:06:23.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Keep a close eye on her to make sure\nthat she doesn't leave the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:33.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you truly that worried\nabout Viscount Morcerf?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.50,0:06:39.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, I will go in your place to inquire\nafter Monsieur Albert's well-being.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:41.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.94,0:06:46.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.98,0:06:52.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bear the thought of a wonderful person\nlike you being disgraced by heartless people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:57.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking everywhere\nfor you, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:07:02.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the middle of a huge scandal, and you\nwalk right into military HQ, the belly of the beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:04.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was one stupid stunt,\nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:15.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"A Word of Advice to General Fernand Morcerf.\NBy Robert Beauchamp."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.77,0:07:22.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to take me\nto Beauchamp's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.48,0:07:23.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.38,0:07:27.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, sorry I kept\nyou guys waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:31.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, what are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.92,0:07:38.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard! All this time, you were\nonly pretending to be my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.79,0:07:40.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Watch out for scandals,"\nmy ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.90,0:07:44.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were planning all along to sell out\nmy father to get your big scoop!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.20,0:07:47.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?!\NRight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:55.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Albert, I'm going tell you everything\nthat I uncovered in my investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.34,0:07:56.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just the plain truth.\NNo lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.95,0:07:59.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So before you do anything rash,\njust hear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.05,0:08:03.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look\nat this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:07.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a copy of a title deed that I bought\nfrom a black-market merchant in the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:11.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I cede ownership of Queen Vasiliki\nof Janina and Princess Haidee..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.16,0:08:13.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"...for the sum of\N100 million Francs."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.83,0:08:16.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Seller, Fernand Mondego."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:19.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this supposed\nto prove?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.90,0:08:23.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I followed the tracks of\nthis "Mondego" person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.47,0:08:26.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But every last bit of information\non him had been erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:30.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was almost as if he\nhad never existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.65,0:08:33.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But Mondego existed,\nall right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.88,0:08:35.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When he returned\nto Marseilles,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.92,0:08:40.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he immediately used the money he\nhad received to purchase orders of nobility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.99,0:08:43.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when he\nchanged his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:45.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Prove it!\NShow me your proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.99,0:08:50.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, I was also able to learn through\NMinistry of the Interior records...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.33,0:08:52.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that Mondego was an old friend\nof Villefort's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:54.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They were both originally\nfrom Marseilles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:09:00.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then Villefort purged all information\nregarding Mondego from all public records.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.84,0:09:03.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how the man known as Mondego\nwas erased from existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:08.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and the man known as Fernand de Morcerf\nwas born in his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.32,0:09:13.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you two saying?! That my father is\nthe same man as that monster, Mondego?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.72,0:09:16.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you two get your kicks by ganging up on\nsomebody and writing about their problems?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.36,0:09:20.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come off it! Do you seriously think I decided to\nhave some fun by writing a made-up article?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.30,0:09:25.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what it did\nto me to write that article?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:29.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think I'm a slimeball who\nwould sell out his friends for a scoop?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.07,0:09:31.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.11,0:09:35.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.74,0:09:40.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have a duty to get the truth out\nto the people, no matter the cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.76,0:09:48.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.23,0:09:55.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou, the immortal man\nliving in the Chateau d'lf...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:09:59.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That mark I saw on the Count's forehead\nthat night in Auteuil...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.40,0:10:02.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...was the mark of Gankutsuou,\nno doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.81,0:10:07.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then does that mean that the Count\nhas turned into Gankutsuou?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:09.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing\nin Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.31,0:10:13.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep pushing yourself this hard,\nyou'll ruin your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.02,0:10:16.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you stay up all night\nagain last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.95,0:10:19.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are a worrywart,\NMaximilien.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:23.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please eat. It's just country food, but it\nwill help you keep your strength up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.66,0:10:25.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that looks great...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:26.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:30.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, take it\nto him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.07,0:10:33.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way!\NI'm too embarrassed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.33,0:10:36.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who said that you\nwanted to meet Franz, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.70,0:10:38.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then you come in\nwith me, big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:40.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And what are you two\nup to out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.71,0:10:41.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:44.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:46.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.85,0:10:50.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here! Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.15,0:10:55.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She said you looked like you were in\nthe dumps, so we made these together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.86,0:11:00.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.27,0:11:40.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mark my words!\NYou'll be next!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.87,0:11:44.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Disaster will come calling\nat your house, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.71,0:11:49.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This feels strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:53.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For there to be so many family members\nin the same house, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.65,0:11:57.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't there a great many people living\nin your own house, Monsieur Franz?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.22,0:12:00.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, maybe.\NThere were lots of servants, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.46,0:12:03.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But now, there's just a few servants\nand my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.93,0:12:05.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.79,0:12:08.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are a lot of different\nkinds of aristocrats.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.76,0:12:13.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The engagement between Valentine and me\nwas forced on us by Monsieur Villefort...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.10,0:12:17.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...just because my family has been known for\ngenerations in Paris as staunch royalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.44,0:12:21.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Albert's family, mine\ndoesn't have a large fortune,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.68,0:12:26.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so we thought it wouldn't hurt to have\nsome backing once I got into diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.78,0:12:30.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I said all those things without knowing\nthe circumstances behind your engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.52,0:12:34.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm not so dumb that I need\nto have you worrying about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:37.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You'd never guess it by looking at me,\nbut I hit the books pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.53,0:12:47.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Noirtier\nsaid it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.34,0:12:53.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that he wanted you to make\NValentine happy in his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.88,0:12:54.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.55,0:13:05.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.72,0:13:09.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father. He passed away\nthree years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.59,0:13:11.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's a beautiful ship\nthat he owned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.29,0:13:15.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She was called the Pharaon.\NShe was the star of our fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.10,0:13:18.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's changed hands now,\nthough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:22.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond Dantes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:26.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Edmond? You know\NEdmond Dantes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.21,0:13:29.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know him?\NYou know who he is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.81,0:13:34.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he worked as first mate\nfor Morrel and Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.06,0:13:46.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No go, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.09,0:13:50.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With that circus out there, I'll never make it\nthrough the front door OR the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.53,0:13:55.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This way, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.94,0:13:58.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.77,0:14:02.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the one gate in the whole mansion\nthat isn't hooked into the security system.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:04.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know\nall this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.55,0:14:06.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Peppo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.72,0:14:10.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get a move on. The paparazzi\nare coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.32,0:14:12.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I owe you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.36,0:14:20.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.30,0:14:23.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there's somebody over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.68,0:14:23.88,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.77,0:14:27.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!\NAre you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.17,0:14:29.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.34,0:14:32.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, aren't you home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.88,0:14:43.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.79,0:14:50.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.29,0:14:52.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother! I'm glad\nyou're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.56,0:14:56.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness you're safe.\NThank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:57.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:15:02.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at how haggard you are.\NI bet you haven't eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.20,0:15:06.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here. I'll have them\nfix something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.81,0:15:09.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Mother. Stop pretending\nthat nothing's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:13.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of people treating me\nlike some clueless kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.75,0:15:17.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hear\nany more lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:26.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fernand and I aren't\ntrue aristocrats.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.33,0:15:32.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We were commoners born in a small village\noutside of Marseilles called Catalonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.83,0:15:34.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:38.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then what is Father's\nreal name?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.17,0:15:45.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your father's real name\nis Fernand Mondego.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.45,0:15:50.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By the time I realized what was happening,\nit was already too late to turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.02,0:15:55.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once I said that we were aristocrats by birth,\NI had no choice but to keep playing the part.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.36,0:15:59.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then the truth finally struck home in the\nmiddle of your father's campaign speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:16:03.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why are you saying these\nthings, too, Mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:06.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you have\nany faith in Father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.77,0:16:12.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the speech given by the Janinan\nprincess that day with my own two ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.17,0:16:16.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I had sensed even for an instant\nthat her words were lies,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.41,0:16:21.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I would have passed judgment over her\nin Heaven's stead right then and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.15,0:16:23.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it was true...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:30.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert... We each must face the consequences\nof the things we have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.89,0:16:33.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We must never be allowed to\navert our eyes from the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.37,0:16:46.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haidee wanted this to happen\nfrom the very beginning!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.41,0:16:49.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!\NDAMN IT!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.71,0:16:55.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, my father and I would go to\nplace flowers on Edmond Dantes' grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:17:02.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father would always stare out at the sea,\nand would never tell me much about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.69,0:17:08.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But as my father lay on his deathbed, he kept\ncalling out his name, tears in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.80,0:17:11.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to see Edmond!\NI want to see Edmond!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.93,0:17:15.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Why wasn't I able\nto save Edmond?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:20.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maximilien, show me Morrel & Son's\ncrew roster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.94,0:17:26.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen many of the records\nthat date back to my father's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.45,0:17:29.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond... Edmond...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.58,0:17:30.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:34.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not him...\NHis face is completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.99,0:17:36.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:37.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it about\nthis person?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:41.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The name Edmond was in\NMonsieur Noirtier's memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:47.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was sent to a prison in deep space\nfor a crime he didn't commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.81,0:17:52.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.94,0:17:56.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Danglars?!\NHe was the ship's purser?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:14.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now I get it...\NSo THAT'S what this is all about...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.83,0:18:18.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get back there, and fast.\NAlbert's in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.93,0:18:21.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world\nis the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.24,0:18:23.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.11,0:18:28.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond Dantes\nis alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.85,0:18:32.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haidee!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:35.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get out here,\NHaidee!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.25,0:18:40.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself!\NHaidee!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.41,0:19:02.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Long time, no see,\nlittle boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.58,0:19:04.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not since we met\nback on Luna, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.35,0:19:07.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Luigi Vampa?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:10.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing\nin the Count's home?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.45,0:19:13.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"What are you doing,"\nhe says...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:16.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This boy's still as wooly-headed\nas ever, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.36,0:19:19.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and explain things\nto him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.97,0:19:31.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you said that you'd\nleft the bandit gang, Peppo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.47,0:19:37.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been keeping an eye on you all this\ntime on the Count's orders, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.18,0:19:42.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've also been sending detailed reports\nof your movements to the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:53.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the Count\ndo such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.26,0:19:56.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you must have\na vague idea by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.10,0:20:01.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,About why the Count made friends with you\non Luna, and then came to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.47,0:20:05.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouth!\NWhere's Haidee?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.57,0:20:07.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and\nsend out Haidee!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.71,0:20:13.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His servants have\nleft the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.45,0:20:18.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Their master is due to arrive\non Earth any time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.26,0:20:31.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"General Morcerf,\nthe Scandal of Janina"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.43,0:20:34.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're making your move,\naren't you, Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.10,0:20:38.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, please stay safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.72,0:20:56.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haidee!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.92,0:23:14.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, you have to tell me.\NWhere can I find hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.06,0:23:17.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the truth\nyou spoke of?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.53,0:23:20.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\nthe Count of Monte Cristo act 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:20.58,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 17:\NThe Confession
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:21.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."The Confession."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.54,0:23:23.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
